{"id": 223704382, "title": "FC Barcelona Fired Xavi For Wanting To Axe These Players, Reports 3Cat", "text": "Share to Facebook Share to Twitter Share to Linkedin Outgoing FC Barcelona head coach Xavi Hernandez was partly fired because of wanting to axe a list of ... [+] players according to 3cat, which cited anonymous sources. Getty Images Outgoing FC Barcelona head coach Xavi Hernandez was partly fired because of wanting to axe a list of players according to 3Cat, which cited anonymous sources. Xavi was dismissed before the weekend, around a month after going back on January decision to step down on June 30. The legendary midfielder agreed to see out his contract until that date in 2025, but negative comments made about Barca's economic situation, and how it hampers being able to keep up with bitter rivals Real Madrid, which has relieved the Catalans of the La Liga and Super Cup titles this term, angered the board. RAC1 reported that Xavi would be dismissed in the coming days, which came to pass a week later after a meeting with Laporta. According to 3cat in Catalonia, however, the remarks Xavi made weren't the only factor at play. Xavi and Laporta reportedly didn't see eye to eye on a list of players that the iconic number 6 didn't want for his sporting project next season, which was led by Robert Lewandowski. SPORT says that this was \"intuited\" by Xavi taking the Pole off in recent matches, which according to Mundo Deportivo caused conflict between the manager and the player. MORE FOR YOU The 83 Best Memorial Day Sales According To Our Deal Savvy Editors The Best Beers In Canada According To The Canadian Brewing Awards NYT \u2018Strands\u2019 #84 Hints, Spangram And Answers For Sunday, May 26th It has also been pretty clear that Xavi didn't want Joao Felix or Vitor Roque either. While Felix was demoted to the bench with right winger Raphinha taking his spot on the left flank, Vitor Roque managed to make just 14 mainly cameo appearances despite Barca agreeing a deal worth north of $60 million with his former club Athletico Paranaense last summer. Oriol Romeu and Marcos Alonso are other names that Xavi didn't count on. Romeu was brought in for a pittance to replace Sergio Busquets while Xavi instead wanted either Joshua Kimmich or Martin Zubimendi that were financially out of reach. And while Romeu still has a contract until 2026, Alonso's expires on June 30 with Barca having in effect confirmed that the former Chelsea man has already played his last game in Blaugrana by not including him in the squad for Sunday's season-ending away trip to Sevilla which is Xavi's last match in charge. Tom Sanderson Following Editorial Standards Print Reprints & Permissions", "summary": "Outgoing FC Barcelona head coach Xavi Hernandez was partly fired because of wanting to axe a list of players according to the Catalan media.", "url": "https://www.forbes.com/sites/tomsanderson/2024/05/26/fc-barcelona-fired-xavi-for-wanting-to-axe-these-players-reports-3cat/", "image": "https://imageio.forbes.com/specials-images/imageserve/6653384befc88276b4c21a39/0x0.jpg?format=jpg&crop=2011,1131,x0,y46,safe&height=900&width=1600&fit=bounds", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-26 13:42:42", "author": "Senior Contributor,Tom Sanderson", "authors": ["Senior Contributor", "Tom Sanderson"], "language": "en", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": 0.009}